.com/2012/07/how-to-make-yogurt/#comment-68711\">08.12.12 at 10:07 am</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>Anon &#8211; I&#8217;m really not sure about them melting or leeching chemicals.  Personally, I don&#8217;t think I would use them.  On top of the possibilities of those things happening, they don&#8217;t transmit heat as well as the glass mason jars, so the incubation probably wouldn&#8217;t be as effective.  You can make it directly in the slow cooker without use of the mason jars, but it just takes a little longer.  Do a google search for &#8220;yogurt slow cooker&#8221; and you&#8217;ll find instructions :)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/07/how-to-make-yogurt/?replytocom=68711#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-68711\", \"68711\", \"respond\", \"13152\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-68775\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\">Anonymous</cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2012/07/how-to-make-yogurt/#comment-68775\">08.15.12 at 9:30 am</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>I tried your recipe with great delight and the yogurt turned out great.  The only change I made was that I used whole milk instead of 2% milk and my yogurt was thicker.  I would however, like for it to be a tad bit thicker so my next batch I plan to use 1/2 whole milk and 