way but now I will keep it and make yogurt! I feel silly for not doing this earlier! It is really easy!  This is exciting because we love love yogurt in our house!  Thank you so much! :D</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/07/how-to-make-yogurt/?replytocom=69382#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-69382\", \"69382\", \"respond\", \"13152\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-69817\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\">Anonymous</cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2012/07/how-to-make-yogurt/#comment-69817\">10.02.12 at 7:29 am</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>Just made yogurt following your instructions the other day, and it&#8217;s great!  I will definitely be making it again soon!  </p>\n<p>I used whole milk, and yogurt from my local Amish market for a starter.  My yogurt came out with a little layer of yellow-ish fatty ick on top.  I love cream-top yogurt, but this isn&#8217;t the same&#8230;wondering whether that&#8217;s a sign of contamination from somewhere, or just what happens with whole milk?  </p>\n<p>Next time I make it I think I will use a different type of yogurt as a starter (I love Stonyfield Farms&#8217; whole milk yogurt), and might try adding powdered milk for thickness.  Thanks for posting!!</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/07/how-to-